(thirdQuint)Biosimilar Erythropoietin in Anaemia Treatment (Maintenance Phase Study).

 This is a prospective, randomized, double blind, parallel group two arm study to establish the therapeutic equivalence, safety and tolerability of EPIAO(R) as compared to EPREX(R) in the treatment of CKD related anaemia in subjects who are on haemodialysis.

 A total of 264 subjects will be randomized into two groups in a 1:1 ratio.

 Treatment arm A will receive EPIAO(R) 1-3 times a week, intravenously for period of 52 weeks and treatment arm B will receive EPREX, 1-3 times a week, intravenously for period of 52 weeks.

